job.description:
Do you have a keen interest in financial markets & financial instruments? Do you want to explore & communicate the impacts of Financial Risks to a bank?
In this position you will have opportunity to:
Build a solid understanding among stakeholders about Financial Risk profile of a bank
(Market, Liquidity, Capital + Counterparty Credit Risk);
Prepare a regular analysis and reports
on the bank's Financial Risk profile in Estonia & Baltics, communicate results to stakeholders & top management;
Continuously contribute to improvements of Financial Risk management processes
, models, governance in Estonia & Baltics;
Grow and develop your competence in Financial Risk management area.
What is needed in this role:
Academic degree in relevant area
;
To have a positive attitude & be strong team-player
;
Ability to work independently, while
actively collaborating with diverse cross-border teams with Risk, Treasury & Markets units
;
Good knowledge of financial markets products, risks & relevant regulations (CRR, EBA, etc);
Fluent in written and spoken English and Estonian
;
Advanced skills in MS Exce
l;
Experience from VBA/SQL/R/Python/Power BI or other similar software is meriting.
With us, you can experience:
Personal and professional growth through self-leadership and continuous development;
Meaningful work that positively impacts our workplace, our customers, and society;
An open and collaborative culture that encourages cross-functional teamwork and provides networking opportunities;
A supportive and inclusive environment that promotes a balanced and sustainable work-life, with flexible working conditions when suitable for the role;
Benefits such as our share based reward program Eken, company pension plan, employee offer for banking products, health insurance.
" Join our team and...
Be a part of engaged team of Financial risk professionals, who serve as
experts in the Estonia and Baltics.
Our work is highly valued to Estonian & Baltic risk management function - we promote a solid risk culture, open communication, create value to our clients and increase Swedbank competitive edge. In our team, we value highly
teamwork
and expect you to be a strong and committed
team-player
as well!
"
Kaur Ilves, your future leader
.
We look forward to your application at 09.12.2025 the latest.
If you are to be employed in Estonia, please note that the salary offered for this position ranges from 3,650-5,450 € gross i.e. before taxes. Read more here!
Swedbank does not discriminate anybody based on gender, age, sexual orientation or sexual identity, ethnicity, religion or disability everybody is welcome.
